Install available Linux updates and upgrades before you install Edge System. In a terminal, run the following commands:

sudo apt -y update sudo apt -y upgrade

If you are an advanced user and would like to run a Docker container, follow the appropriate procedure:
•	Create Linux x64 Docker container
•	Create Linux ARM Docker container

1. 	
With root privileges, open a terminal.
2. 	
Install Edge System with the sudo apt -y install command. For example to install the Linux ARM Debian package, run command:

sudo apt -y install ./EdgeSystem_linux-arm.deb

3. 	
When prompted, type in your password and press Enter.

Edge System is installed on your Linux computer.

